5:
To Weihu, the Bloodcrazed, and the
Crimson Blades...
7:
To think that the boss himself has
seen fit to chase me all the way
here!
10:
Oh, their longing for me simply
bleeds off the page! Hahaha!
16:
...And so my former boss has called
upon me. Summoned me, really.
19:
Tsk... Those bastards. Taking kids
from your hometown hostage is
some depraved stuff.
22:
Surprisingly vindictive of him, I must
say. I fear he won't be content until
he's ground my very bones to dust.
26:
I suppose I will have to take my
leave for the time being. I look
forward to being in your company
again—if I make it back.
31:
W-wait a second! The note
mentioned the Crimson Blades too,
didn't it?
35:
It did. I believe they saw you in our
previous engagement.
39:
Then this matter concerns us just as
much as it does you. We cannot
simply overlook a hostage situation!
43:
You are aware that certain death
awaits you if you come with me, are
you not?
45:
They've moved beyond their own
territory and reached other Floats.
That means they're serious this time.
47:
I'm the one they're truly after. The
boss will likely be satisfied with just
my head.
51:
Fact is, our names were on the
paper. They called us out—we've got
a right to go.
54:
I'm just saying, leaving the matter to
me seems the most—
58:
Now hold on a minute. Would YOU
be okay with sending someone else
to fight your battles for you?
60:
No, you wouldn't. Besides, don't
worry. None of us plan on dying.
63:
That's right, we don't. And neither do
you, right, Weihu?
68:
Well. I suppose it can't be helped
then. I hope you're prepared for
what's to come.
74:
Already out in droves, huh. That's
some welcoming party...
78:
We've still got a ways to go until the
warehouse district.
82:
With that in my mind, I'll have to ask
you most respectfully to deal with
this riff-raff for me.
87:
N-now hold on! Weihu, where are
you going?!
90:
You wish to keep your lives, no? In
that case, you'll need to handle this
unruly lot first!
96:
Damn him... Thinking he can do
whatever he wants like that...
99: Hey! You're in our damn way!
103:
Why hello there, Boss. Long time no
see. Have you lost weight?
107:
Oh... Oh, it hurts! How it stings! I've
been shot again.
109:
Heh... Hehehehe.... Is this really any
way to treat a person?
112:
You're not a person, Weihu. You're a
monster. A mad dog that needs to
be put down.
114:
Hahaha... Yes, yes, I understand now.
We monsters... we're scary, aren't
we? I can smell the fear on you.
117:
You were terrified... Of the day you'd
find yourself staring down the barrel
of my gun. Of the ear-piercing pull
of the trigger...
120:
Horrifying, isn't it? The darkness...
When the lights go out, there's
NOTHING. That's why we kill. To keep
the fear at bay...
123:
You and your imagination. It's far
simpler than that—you are no
longer convenient to me. That's why
you must die.
124:
You know how this city works.
Monsters that are no longer useful
die alone. That's how it's always
been.
131:
Aha... Hahaha! Oh, Boss... How little
you understand!
135:
I'm all alone, yes! All I know is me.
There's nothing else—and that's
exactly why I HAVE to win!
138:
Because it's so unspeakably
terrifying... the pale face of death
staring directly at me! I HAVE TO
CONQUER IT.
141:
Let's see then... Can I outrun the
reaper one more time? Ahaha!
AHAHAHA!
153:
You're mad. All you bring is death
and suffering... everywhere you go.
158:
But, Boss, don't you see... The world is
SO much bigger than we thought!
160:
And in it are these people... Who
would be willing to care after a
monster. Who'd adopt a mad dog
like me!
163:
Well, it was fun while it lasted, Boss.
Really. I had some great times
working for you.
165:
But unfortunately for you... It seems
I'll live to die another day.
171:
Come now.
It was you who pulled the trigger
first.
182:
Oh, hello there, everyone. I'm glad to
see you're all well.
186:
You owe us big time for that stunt
you just pulled.
195:
Hehe. No killing—that's your way of
doing things, right? I played by your
rules.
201:
So what happened? Are you
satisfied?
205:
Yes. I very much am. I won. I
conquered fear.
207:
What a terrible pastime. Bringing
death and suffering to all... Is that
who I am?
212: I'm not so sure about that.
221:
They've got you to thank for saving
them. Say, I don't suppose you
happen to be good with kids?
225:
Ahahaha. Not even remotely. 
This is one battle I can't win.
